column15:
Ashley was shot in the head. Her body was then moved and dumped at Ellery and Canfield roads.

Her age is unknown, she was only described as a young transgender woman in a press release.

Cameron died by suicide after telling their mum that they wanted to be a girl.

> A BOY of 10 has been found hanged at his South Yorkshire home after telling his mum he wanted to be a girl. Tragic Cameron McWilliams had already asked for permission to wear make-up, and been teased after he was found wearing his half-sister's knickers. His desperate mum Kelly McWilliams told a Doncaster inquest she had bought him girls' underwear to wear in private, but had refused his requests to be allowed to wear make-up. She said: "It was apparent he was unhappy and said he wanted to be a girl. He did like girls' things." Mrs McWilliams told a Doncaster inquest Cameron was older than his years and had expressed an interest in transvestism. He had been teased after once being found in his half-sister's knickers, and had asked if he could wear make-up. His mum told him he would have to wait until he was older. 
> 
> Although Cameron had not been a happy child, she did not think he was depressed.
> 
> "He said he wanted to be a girl, and he did like girls’ things. He used to tell us that he wanted to be a scientist. He was a very loving and very caring boy. We can’t think of a reason he would have wanted to do this".

Cameron's suicide was not recorded on the official TDoR 2008 list collated by https://tdor.info.

Lawrence was shot to death by a classmate because he wore women's clothing.

The victim and her housemate were tied up by two men who invaded their home in quadro 708/709 norte. Both were stabbed, but her housemate survived and was taken to hospital.

The victim's death was not recorded on the official TDoR 2008 list collated by https://tdor.info.

Luna's body was found in a dumpster next to the N250 Loures-Montemor highway on Thursday 28th February.

Her body showed signs of aggression and was sent for autopsy. It is believed that she was killed elsewhere and her body dumped.

> The body was discovered by an employee of Resotrans - Collection and Transportation of Solid Waste, when he arrived at the company that is located on a field off the National Highway 250 (Estrada Loures-Montemor). It was 7:17 am and the official, after seeing the body in one of several containers of rubble, decided to go to the PSP, the Loures squad, and alert the authorities who immediately, came to the scene.
> 
> Realising that it was a homicide, they closed the area and called the Judiciary Police, who, at the end of yesterday afternoon, still did not know the identity of the victim. "She had no documents," a PC source told CM, reaffirming that it is a [trans woman's] corpse - the PSP announced that it was a woman - and that the causes and circumstances that led to her death. The body, which had some marks of aggression, will be autopsied. Found inside a container in Loures, the victim was killed elsewhere and the body was transported there. "At least that is what can be concluded through the remains found there," he told the CM police source.

Luna reportedly frequented the Conde Redondo area of Lisbon.
